This paper is about relation classification in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a framework based on recurrent neural networks (RNN) for this task, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the limitations of the SemEval-2010 Task 8 dataset, which is a common benchmark for relation classification, indicating a potential interest in natural language processing (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
